pective on the history of St. Petersburg on the eve of revolution and presents a fresh view of Russia's experience of modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCity and town lifezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aModernism (Aesthetics)zRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aPopular culturezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aSocial changezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030016504340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016570840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300165708423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300165708/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY